<h1>Pyramid</h1>
<p><img src="/static/img/pyramid.png" class="img-float img-thumbnail"/>
Welcome to <code>${project}</code>, an application generated by
the <a href="http://pylonsproject.org/">Pyramid</a> Web Framework.</p>

<p>Project templates called <code>ziggurat</code> is intended to
allow you to create a web that requires login.
Yes, we use the library <a href="https://pypi.python.org/pypi/ziggurat-foundations">Ziggurat Foundations</a>
for providing a variety of tools for setting permissions.</p>

<p>Using <a href="http://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/pyramid_chameleon">Chameleon</a>
as HTML generator makes writing more comfortable in the HTML templates. This is
because the syntax has to follow the rules of SGML, so it looks natural as
HTML tags, but it's not.</p>

<p>Form generator using <a href="http://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/deform/">Deform</a> 2
which facilitate the writing of validation and auto-completion. It uses the
<a href="http://getbootstrap.com">Bootstrap</a> 3 that put
comfort in the smartphone display but still comfortably viewed on a desktop.</p>

